{"ts":"2026-07-19T03:42:50.641Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"append","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"GH-606. .toon item files use count-prefixed array headers (notes[N]{...}, tags[N], tests[N]); concurrent commutative appends hard-conflict, and hand-resolution with a stale count makes the item unreadable by pm get while validate skips it silently (pm-cxyv). Authoritative-state twin of pm-wc1r (history layer). Fix direction: .toon-aware merge driver or count-header-free serialization; at minimum validate must hard-fail on header/data disagreement."},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-19T03:42:50.641Z"}],"before_hash":"08336745922a43102681242f9b489b317ac120f33583fed2a65d7d41df39433d","after_hash":"ba5874274178d30dabaf305b3cae57828c572dd77cde0bffd2241632b8f370f7"}
